Nigeria’s SEC Gets Notices on Planned Acquisitions of 3 Bailed Out Banks

-- B y   E m e l e   O n u
-- 
2011-08-23T16:27:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/nigeria-s-sec-gets-notices-on-planned-acquisitions-of-3-bailed-out-banks.html
Nigeria’s Securities and Exchange
Commission received notices on the planned acquisitions of three
lenders bailed out by the country’s central bank in 2009, Lanre
Oloyi, a spokesman for the capital market regulator, said in a
telephone interview today from Abuja.  The lenders include Union Bank of Nigeria Plc, being
acquired by African Capital Alliance, and  Oceanic Bank
International Plc (OCEANIC) , being bought by  Ecobank Transnational Inc. (ETI) 
The third is  Finbank Plc (FIRSTINL) , being taken over by  First City
Monument Bank Plc (FCMB) , he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emele Onu in Johannesburg at 
 eonu1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
